@*
    The Nxt Blazor root component.

    MapRazorComponents<Root>() renders this for every page request. Pages discovered by the
    source generator are decorated with [Route("...")] (and, if interactive, with a
    [RenderModeXxx] attribute), so Blazor's Router finds them via reflection in the user's
    assembly. The Router renders the matched page using its declared render mode.

    For server-interactive pages, Blazor wraps the rendered HTML in <!--Blazor:server,...-->
    markers and the embedded blazor.web.js boots a SignalR connection to /_blazor, which
    AddInteractiveServerRenderMode() maps for us.
*@
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <base href="/" />
    <title>Nxt</title>
    <HeadOutlet />
</head>
<body>
    <Router AppAssembly="typeof(Nxt.Components.Root).Assembly" AdditionalAssemblies="Nxt.NxtStartupBridge.UserAssemblies">
        <Found Context="routeData">
            <RouteView RouteData="routeData" DefaultLayout="null" />
            <FocusOnNavigate RouteData="routeData" Selector="h1" />
        </Found>
        <NotFound>
            <h1 style="font-family:system-ui;padding:2rem">404 — Not found</h1>
        </NotFound>
    </Router>
    <script src="_framework/blazor.web.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
